[[!meta title="Numerous security holes in Tails 3.8"]]
[[!pagetemplate template="news.tmpl"]]

[[!tag security/fixed]]

Several security holes that affect Tails 3.8 are now fixed in Tails 3.9.

We **strongly** encourage you to
[[upgrade to Tails 3.9|news/version_3.9]] as soon as possible.

 - Tor Browser: [[!mfsa 2018-21]]
 - Thunderbird: [[!mfsa 2018-19]]
 - Linux and intel-microcode:
   - [[!cve CVE-2018-3620]] aka. Foreshadow aka. L1 Terminal Fault
   - too many other CVEs to list them all here
 - CUPS: [[!debsa2018 4243]]
 - Exiv2: [[!debsa2018 4238]]
 - FUSE: [[!debsa2018 4257]]
 - GDM: [[!debsa2018 4270]]
 - libsoup: [[!debsa2018 4241]]
 - Imagemagick: [[!debsa2018 4245]]
 - ffmpeg: [[!debsa2018 4258]]
 - libmspack: [[!debsa2018 4260]]
 - Samba: [[!debsa2018 4271]]
 - Apache XML Security for C++ library: [[!debsa2018 4265]]
 - OpenSSH: [[!debsa2018 4280]]
